	abstract = {We present results from a near-infrared spectroscopic study of candidate 
brown dwarfs and low-mass stars in the young cluster NGC 2024. Using
FLAMINGOS on the KPNO 2.1 m and 4 m telescopes, we have obtained spectra
of {\textasciitilde}70 new members of the cluster and classified them via the prominent
J- and H-band water absorption features. Derived spectral types range
from {\textasciitilde}M1 to later than M8 with typical classification errors of 0.5-1
