    fate of some massive stars. We discuss the ongoing challenge of chemical
    diffusion in the strongly coupled plasma regime, and exhibit
    improvements in MESA that now allow for the simulation of radiative
    levitation of heavy elements in hot stars. We close by noting that the
    MESA software infrastructure provides bit-for-bit consistency for all
